It seems like I get the same issue if I run this code:
```typescript
  const table = worksheet.addTable({
    name: 'Holdliste',
    ref: 'A3',
    headerRow: true,
    style: {
      theme: 'TableStyleDark3',
      showRowStripes: true,
    },
    columns: [
      { name: 'foo' },
      { name: 'bar' },
      { name: 'qux' },
    ],
    rows: [
      // [1, 2, 3]
    ],
  });
  table.commit();
```

But not if I add a row
```typescript
  const table = worksheet.addTable({
    name: 'Holdliste',
    ref: 'A3',
    headerRow: true,
    style: {
      theme: 'TableStyleDark3',
      showRowStripes: true,
    },
    columns: [
      { name: 'foo' },
      { name: 'bar' },
      { name: 'qux' },
    ],
    rows: [
       [1, 2, 3]
    ],
  });
  table.commit();
```

This is in the desktop version of excel - I would assume this potentially has something to do with empty-row tables not working.
